The question as to who would convene the plebeian assembly, if there were no tribunes, is one that is wrapped in the deepest obscurity. One occasion, when the difficulty must certainly have arisen, is in 449 ac, after the termination of the decemvirate ⁴. This, however, is a subject which I do not feel myself competent to discuss.
